      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my ac unit outside is doing something weird. the fan is making this loud humming sound but the blades arent actually spinning. what could be causing that and is it safe to go out there and look at it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A humming AC unit can be quite unsettling, especially when the blades aren't spinning. It's not uncommon for a unit to produce a humming noise when it's not running, but it's still worth investigating. You might want to check the capacitor, as it could be causing the hum. It's a bit like a mischievous little goblin, quietly humming away, but not doing much of anything productive. \n\nHowever, if the humming noise is coming from the compressor or the fan motor, it's generally not a good idea to go out there and look at it, as it could be a safety hazard. You might want to consider calling a professional to take a closer look. They'll be able to diagnose the issue and make the necessary repairs without putting themselves or others at risk. \n\nIn the meantime, you can try to isolate the issue by turning off the power to the unit at the circuit breaker or fuse box. This will prevent any further damage or potential electrical shock. Just be careful not to get too close to the unit while it's still humming away, or you might get zapped by a stray spark.",
